name: Agent quality standard — self-test, first principles, coordination hooks
description: Every spawned agent must self-test output, reason from first principles, bring coordination/context/validation back. No unchecked claims.
type: feedback
---

Every agent must:
1. **Self-test** — verify own output before returning. Re-read files, check completeness, confirm claims.
2. **First-principles reasoning** — don't pattern-match. Reason from the actual problem. Justify every conclusion.
3. **Bring coordination** — flag cross-page dependencies, collation needs, blocking items. Don't just do the task — connect it to the whole.
4. **Bring context** — surface prior decisions, IA mapping, relevant research for the current work item.
5. **Validate** — check claims against live files, not from memory. "I checked" means ran a command or read a file in this session.
6. **Cite sources** — every factual claim has a file path + line, command output, or explicit "unverified."

**Why:** Alison said "SICK OF LOW STANDARD SHIT" and "anything coming back to me better have been first-principles considered, critically thought through and high quality. AGENTS TEST THEMSELVES."

**How to apply:** Include these requirements in every agent prompt. Agents that can't meet this bar return "I couldn't verify X" rather than guessing.
